# Warren Bot weekly run.
# TZ comes from the container's TZ env var (set in docker-compose.yml).
# Sunday 18:00 local time. Adjust to taste.
#
# What this line does:
#  1. cd into the app
#  2. run the bot (writes out/preview.html, out/picks.csv, emails, syncs Notion)
#  3. snapshot the result into out/archive/YYYY-MM-DD.html
#  4. regenerate out/index.html listing every archived run
#
# All stdout/stderr goes to /var/log/warren.log, which entrypoint.sh tails so
# the output shows up in `docker compose logs bot`.

0 18 * * 0 root cd /app && warren-bot run && cp out/preview.html "out/archive/$(date +\%Y-\%m-\%d).html" && /app/deploy/build-index.sh >> /var/log/warren.log 2>&1

# Trailing newline is required for cron to accept the file.
